The paper deals with the construction of error-correcting codes, specifically the C-Code, which is a type of cyclic lowest-density MDS array code. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the underlying connections between C-Codes and starters in group theory, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of C-Codes involves the use of cyclic symmetry, which is a topic in discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the suitability of C-Codes for RAID 6, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and storage systems (cs.SI).
